title: For Sale:  Springfield Model 951, .410 ga.,
postcontent:
This is a Springfield Model 951, .410 ga., 24" bbl  Item G-30552-4

Long out of production, the 951 is what some might call a utility gun. Made for the lowest end of the market, this single-shot bolt action shotgun is chambered for 2 1/2 and 3 inch 410 gauge shells.

Manufactured by the Savage Arms Corporation from early 1960's until perhaps 1971, it is essentially the same shotgun as the Stevens model 51 except that it has a hard plastic butt plate instead of the ventilated rubber butt pad found on the Stevens Model 51.
Brass 410 Ga. Shells.

Springfield Model 951 Bolt Action Shotgun
Springfield 951
Overall Length (inches) 	43.5
Weight (lbs) 	5.1
Action Type 	Bolt Action Turn Bolt
Length of Pull(inches) 	14.5
Barrel Length (inches) 	24.0
Cartridge 	410 gauge, 2 1/2 and 3 inch shells
Magazine Capacity 	Single shot

All Springfield Model 951 and Stevens Model 51's came with a fixed full choke. There is a simple automatic safety which engages when the bolt is opened. After a cartridge is chambered, the safety tab above the bolt handle must be pushed down to fire the gun.
To remove the bolt, the receiver/barrel assembly must be dismounted from the stock and the bolt stop screw removed from the bottom of the receiver. 

We have additional higher resolution pictures of this item available upon request.

Call REDACTED or come by Green Country Arms & Pawn in Tulsa, OK, (9075 E 31st St, Tulsa, OK). Be sure to mention that you saw our ad on Armslist.

We can also ship to a FFL dealer. Shipping is $20 for all hand guns and $40 for long guns in the lower 48 states. We do NOT ship to CA. We will ship to NY, CO, CT or any other state within the restrictions of those states. If you have a question, please ask. Payment can be made using a credit card (NO Am. Ex.), by phone or with postal money order (upon clearing). We are currently not accepting personal checks. 

You can also come check out our guns, ammo and accessories in person at our store M-F 9am - 6pm, Sat 10am - 5pm. We're closed on Sundays.

We also buy and trade firearms.  We now have a searchable Real-Time firearms inventory database at www.greencountryarms.com/Firearms.  Check out some of our other guns.

title: For Sale:  Pristine Argentinian FAL w/ SA battle pack and 4 mags
postcontent:
For sale is an original Argentine 50.00 FAL semi automatic rifle parts kit. I say parts kit because legally it cannot be assembled into a rifle until 6 more American parts are installed. A FAL needs a 7 or more American made parts to become compliant, I've already added the American made Combo device/flash hider.  My goal was to keep this rifle as original as possible on the outside and use American made on the inside. If this is your kit you can assemble it anyway you wish.  If you need guidance or assistance I can help as time permits. 

These rifles were imported and BATF ruled that they could not be sold as rifles but as kits with the uppers going to one distributor and the lowers and bolt carrier groups going to another.   I've gathered the rare components now the rest is up to you.

This kit may have been fired for testing purposes only in Argentina but has never been issued and then sitting in my gun safe since 2007. If you've ever wanted to own as close to issued, FAL licensed manufactured rifle this is it.

The bill of sale will state that this was sold to you as a parts kit and not to be assembled until it has the proper amount of 922(r) parts needed for BATF compliance. 

Cash only no trades.

title: For Sale:  New in Box ATI FX45 1911 LW FB (lightweight Fatboy). A perfect lighter carry and concealed size 12+1 rounds of 45Cal
postcontent:
Chances are you will not find another of these in town, so buy yourself a 13 round 1911 Pistol. Excellent for concealed carry because it is lightweight and packs 13 rounds of 45 ACP.  These LW FB model guns were produced in 2013.

I have a new in the box ATI LW FB 45 caliber. LW FB stands for LightWeight Fat Boy. Will hold 12 rounds plus 1. Called a fatboy because of the double stacked magazine, but really no wider than a single stack 1911. This 1911 is perfect for concealed carry as it is much smaller and much lighter than a regular full size 1911. Be over 21,have a FL drivers License and I will fill out a bill of sale. Not looking for trades. $625.

FX45 Fatboy Lightweight .45ACP 3.2 Inch Flared Bull Barrel Blue Finish Combat Sights 12 Round

Designed on the 1911 platform with a wide-body frame. Ambidextrous safety. 3.2 inch flared bull barrel with blued finish. Carbon steel slide with front and rear serrations. Lowered and flared ejection port. Combat sights dovetailed into the slide. Dual recoil-spring system. extended slide catch. Beavertail grip safety. Skeletonized aluminum trigger. Lightweight alloy frame. Ultra-thin polymer grip panel.

Manufactuer: American Tactical Imports
Model: FX45 Fatboy Lightweight
Caliber: .45 ACP
Barrel Length: 3.2
Capacity: 12 + 1
Finish: Blue
Hand Gun Web Model: FX45

Overall length under seven inches, 5.5 inches high and only 1.33 inches at its widest point, the FX45 is easy to conceal even under light clothing. But it’s a true 1911 and has all of the excellent features John Moses Browning designed into his original pistol: single-action trigger, excellent ergonomics and well-placed controls that are easy to operate.
The machined steel slide has dual sets of grasping grooves, and the ejection port has been lowered and flared to ensure that spent cases get out of the way surely and quickly.
But the most modern feature is that it uses a bushing-less barrel with a flared muzzle section. Another departure from the original is a telescoping, dual-spring recoil system on a full-length guide rod. Both of these features ensure tight and consistent barrel/slide lockup for improved accuracy and functioning. It also greatly simplifies disassemble.
The low-profile rear sight has a large, easy-to-acquire square notch and is angled to prevent it from hanging up on clothing on the draw, and its rear face is serrated to reduce glare. The front is a square blade with a white dot insert.
The alloy frame pares the Fatboy LW’s unloaded weight to a mere 22 ounces, and the frame is undercut at the trigger guard to permit a high grip on the gun.
The ambidextrous thumb safety levers are smaller than normally seen on a 1911 but can still be operated positively. An extended beavertail grip safety with a palm swell provides superior handling while ameliorating recoil—a nice feature on a .45 pistol weighing so little. Aggressively checkered, polymer grip panels allow a secure grip.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1956 AYM Czech VZ52 Rifle, 7.62x45 w/ 420 rounds
postcontent:
Produced in Slovania prior to the Russian push to adopt 7.62x39, this is a VZ52 chambered in 7.62x45. 1 Detachable magazine, 100% functional buttstock S spring to store field cleaning kit, sling and 420 rounds of Ammo (16x 15 round original surplus boxes plus loose rounds). This rifle has a crisp trigger, no breaks or cracks in the stock with the regular imported dings and bumps to be expected. Side folding bayonet is extremely tight and rock solid when it swings out. A very cool design feature.

Many of the VZ52's were ruined visually by coating them in a flaky bedliner paint (see GunBroker), but this one was left unscathed. Most in this country are marked "SHE" for the Bohemian production facility, but this is significantly less common. Bolt locks back positively, the action is VERY smooth considering the age/technology that made it, and magazine rocks into place solidly without a fight.

I am paring down my weapons to rifles my wife can hold more easily, and this is outside the range of her arms (my efforts to make her lift more... failed). I really like to even pull this rifle out to look at, and it is a hit with enthusiasts and people who know nothing. It just has a great feel. Some have compared it to the SKS, but I feel like it is further upstream with a feeling more like an M1 variant. Definitely could be a stock refinishing project.
